Package: MUSE
Title: MusicXML Unpacking for Statistical Evidence
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Muhammad", "Rehan", , "rehanmuh@g.ucla.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Ingests MusicXML vocal scores and converts them into explicit,
    analysis-ready tabular encodings of musical events (notes, rests, ties,
    grace notes, durations, meter), pitch representations (MIDI, pitch class,
    interval, contour), and lyric underlay (syllable boundaries, melisma spans,
    word boundaries) aligned to the exact note(s) that realize each lyric
    segment. From these encodings it derives interpretable text-setting
    features (stress-to-beat alignment, melismatic density, melodic contour,
    tone-melody correspondence) and provides modular interfaces to permutation
    tests, GAM/spline models ('mgcv'), and GLMMs ('lme4' or 'brms'), with
    plotting helpers. The architecture separates the XML-dependent reader from
    pure transformation logic so that any component can be replaced or extended.
